http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Thiruvananthapuram/Minister-to-take-up-SCTIMST-issue/article13987753.ece

Health Minister V.S. Sivakumar has said that he will meet Union Minister for Science and Technology Harshvardhan in New Delhi on January 8 and present a memorandum appealing the Central government to intervene to resolve the huge financial strain faced by Sree Chitra Tirunal Institute for Medical Sciences and Technology (SCTIMST).The decision to increase user charges by the SCTIMST would make advanced treatment facilities in the institution unaffordable to many, Mr. Sivakumar said in a statement here on Thursday.He said that he would also give a memorandum to Union Health Minister J.P. Nadda to help SCTIMST by increasing Central allocation to the institution.